data.description: Stylish Colonial home in the Downingtown Area School District! 9 Edgewood Dr has it all, from a convenient location with a private wooded homesite on a cul-de-sac, to a spacious floorplan with beautiful finishes. This is a classic center-hall layout with formal living and dining rooms, a family room with a wood burning fireplace, and a spacious eat-in kitchen that opens onto a screened porch and the back deck. Simply elegant living spaces with beautiful hardwood floors, built-in bookshelves in the family room, crown molding, dining room chair rail, and great natural light throughout. The kitchen is a welcoming space to entertain with chic white cabinets, contrasting black granite counters, and stainless steel appliances. The 1st floor also features an updated powder room and a beautifully designed laundry room with a sink and excellent storage. Upstairs, there are 4 bedrooms and 2 full bathrooms including a spacious owner’s retreat with a walk-in closet, ceiling fan and en suite bathroom. Downstairs, there is a finished basement that will give you amazing opportunities to expand your living space. You could easily set up a dedicated home office, rec room, home theater, workout space, or so much more. Plus, the basement offers plenty of additional storage. What a lovely home – tucked into a wooded neighborhood setting with easy access to Rte 30, Rte 100 and the PA Turnpike. You can enjoy a diverse selection of nearby shops and restaurants with Eagleview Town Center minutes away, plus you’ll have hiking, boating, and recreation opportunities at nearby Marsh Creek State Park. 9 Edgewood Dr also features a newer roof and hot water heater, central air, a 1-car garage, and private driveway parking. This home deserves a personal visit. Request a tour today!
